snippet.textDisplay: I love that black dress!! I wouldn’t wear the white one I would just wear that black starry night dress. It’s stunning , modern with gothic and Victorian details and its classy absolutely stunning!!  I got married 22 years ago and 22 years ago wearing black to ur wedding ( at least in the U.S.)wasn’t heard of! No one had worn one yet. I’m a Wiccan Witch and back then u didn’t say that out loud. I was raised Catholic. But I’ve always worn black and I was gothic before gothic was a thing lol I was gothic when u were considered weird but I love weird cause that means ur unique and u will never blend in the crowd! So we wanted just us and my best friend his dad n my mom and our 4 year old son of course. It was our day and I wasn’t waisting money on a wedding that ends up being a party for everyone else but u. It’s about us not other ppl. And then when I got to the church I was wearing a whole black dress w lace and with accents of gold with a handkerchief bottom. That only thing I have up was we got married in October and we had a judge and we were gonna get married up in the mountains in autumn would be beautiful but my Catholic mother and his very Christian dad genuinely asked us one favor to them if we can please get married in a church. My husband was dead set against it and I told him look it Atheist and I’m Wiccan neither of us share the Christian and catholic beliefs so if we don’t believe in it what hard would it do to make them happy. It means nothing to us but the world to them. So we found a mondi nondenominational church n the pastor married us with a combo of  his stuff and what I gave him. And everyone was happy. Except my mother almost passed out when I showed up in a white dress. Lol I said “ mother we’re in a church that was what u asked from me. If u like we can leave n I’ll call the judge and wear white?!” She said no it’s fine. Lol but 20 years ago the looks u would get it was like if u wore black for ur wedding gown they acted like the church would melt! Lol n now were cool as hell black lipstick is done by all the high end brands in makeup now mean wile i had to get mine as a teenager from NYC or wet n wild lol

snippet.textDisplay: 24:03 Your dress looks absolutely divine. (I won an argument in a Colour Theory class over the 'colour' black. Black and white are not considered 'colours' (technically) as they are the 'ends' of the colour spectrum. B-U-T, colour is perceived by the 'eye'. I asked the instructor, 'Can you see it? Can you see the colour black? Can you see the colour white?' He responded. 'Yes, I can see the colours black and white.' I said, 'Then they are colours, if the eye can 'see' it'. He conceded. My piece was a monochromatic of black. Rim shot 🥁💃)
